713133f-a.title: Manhattan: 43rd Street - 3rd Avenue
713133f-a.text:
43rd Street, north side, west from Third Avenue. The view is cut
off by the Grand Central Terminal, west of Lexington Avenue.
October 11, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

713134f-a.title: Manhattan: 43rd Street - 3rd Avenue
713134f-a.text:
43rd Street, south side, clearing adjoining the S. E. corner of
Third Avenue. This clearing goes through the block, disclosing
Public School No. 27 in the corresponding position on the
south side of 42nd Street.
February 2, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

713141f-a.title: Manhattan: 43rd Street (East) - 3rd Avenue
713141f-a.text:
St. Agnes' Roman Catholic Church, 145 East 43rd Street, north side,
between Third and Lexington Avenues.
March 18, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

708071f-a.title: Manhattan: 3rd Avenue - 43rd Street
708071f-a.text:
Third Avenue at and adjoining the S. W. corner of 43rd Street,
showlng 676 Third Avenue, the corner house, a three-story
frame house with a stucco front.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection,Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 540

713138f-a.title: Manhattan: 43rd Street (East) - 3rd Avenue
713138f-a.text:
152 East 43rd Street, south side, just west of Third Avenue,
a three story frame house. The tall building at the right is the
Daily News Building,on 42nd Street.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York
Negative No. 541

713135f-a.title: Manhattan: 43rd Street (East) - 3rd Avenue
713135f-a.text:
213-201 East 43rd Street, adjoining and at the N.E. corner of
Third Avenue. Nos. 209 and 211 (the latter may be identified
by a man sitting on the coorstep) are later to be demolished
for a new "automobile hotel' to be built by the Kent Automatic
Garage Company.
July 25, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

713136f-b.title: Manhattan: 43rd Street (East) - 3rd Avenue
713136f-b.text:
(1)
209, 211-215 East 43rd Street, north side, east of Third Avenue.
Nos. 209 and 211 (the latter may be identified by a man sit-
ting on the doorstep) are later to be demolished for a new
"automobile hotel" to be built by the Kent Automatic Garage
Company.
July 25, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, seen from across the clearing on the south side.
January 7, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

713137f-a.title: Manhattan: 43rd Street (East) - 3rd Avenue
713137f-a.text:
207, 205, 203 East 43rd Street, adjoining the N.E. corner of
Third Avenue, seen from the clearing on the south side.
December 14, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
